==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English ''Christ's cross''
===Verb===
'''to crisscross'''  (''transitive'' and ''intransitive'')
# to move [[back and forth]] (over something)
# to mark something with [[crossed]] [[line]]s
===Noun===
'''crisscross'''
# a [[pattern]] of crossed lines
===Adjective===
'''crisscross'''
# [[marked]] with crossed lines
===Adverb===
'''crisscross'''
# [[crossing]] one another

